label.value: adult mediodorsal antennal lobe neuron D1

value.value: Giant neuron of the adult antennal lobe that receives a large amount of input in the lateral accessory lobe and the crepine (Hulse et al., 2021). It has presynaptic sites in many regions across the protocerebrum (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: lobula columnar neuron LC33

value.value: Atypical adult lobula columnar neuron that sends output to the lateral accessory lobe (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: lobula columnar neuron LC27

value.value: Adult lobula columnar neuron that sends output to a glomerular region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: LC27 optic glomerulus

value.value: Optic glomerulus formed by the axon terminals of lobula columnar (LC) 27 neurons (Hulse et al., 2021. It is found in the posterior lateral protocerebrum (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult lateral accessory lobe-contralateral nodulus 2 neuron

value.value: Adult neuron that mainly receives input in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe and has its presynaptic sites in contralateral nodulus 2 (Hulse et al., 2021). There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it is a primary neuron of the DALv3 lineage (Kandimalla et al., 2023).

label.value: adult lateral accessory lobe-wedge-ipsilateral nodulus 2 neuron

value.value: Adult neuron that mainly receives input in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe, with some extensions into the neighboring wedge and ventromedial neuropils (Hulse et al., 2021). It has its presynaptic sites in ipsilateral nodulus 2 (Hulse et al., 2021). There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it develops from the BAMv1 (LALv1) neuroblast (Kandimalla et al., 2023). It is glutamatergic (Lu et al., 2022).

label.value: adult posterior lateral protocerebrum-dorsal accessory calyx projection neuron

value.value: Adult neuron that receives input in the posterior lateral protocerebrum and has outputs in the dorsal accessory calyx, superior lateral protocerebrum and superior clamp (Li et al., 2020). It does not target the mushroom body ventral accessory calyx or main calyx (Li et al., 2020). There are approximately 13 of these cells per hemisphere, with their cell bodies close to the lateral horn (Li et al., 2020). They collectively provide substantial input to alpha/beta posterior Kenyon cells (Li et al., 2020).

definition.value: Corresponds to three hemibrain types (SLP360, SLP362, SLP371 - based on neuprint bodyIDs), but subtypes are not further characterized by Li et al. (2020).

label.value: adult doublesex aDN (male) neuron

value.value: Adult doublesex aDN neuron of the male (Nojima et al., 2021). Its lateral (input) arbor is mainly restricted to the anterior optic tubercle, where it receives input from LC10a neurons (Nojima et al., 2021). It is involved in approaching and facing the female during courtship (Nojima et al., 2021).

label.value: adult doublesex aDN (female) neuron

value.value: Adult doublesex aDN neuron of the female (Nojima et al., 2021). Its lateral (input) neurites are mainly found in the posterior part of the superior lateral protocerebrum, with minor processes in the superior clamp and ventrolateral protocerebrum (Nojima et al., 2021). It receives multimodal sensory information, including inputs from a range of antennal lobe projection neurons (Nojima et al., 2021). It also receives substantial input from the oviposition excitatory and inhibitory neurons and is involved in egg-laying site selection (Nojima et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-round body neuron

value.value: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge (PB), mixed terminals in layers 3, 4 and 5 of a fan-shaped body column, and presynaptic or mixed terminals in the round body (Lin et al., 2013; Wolff et al., 2015; Wolff and Rubin, 2018; Hulse et al., 2021). These cells are found in PB glomeruli 1-8, but not 9 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). There are two subtypes, one that has a phase shift in connectivity between PB glomeruli and FB columns and one that does not (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-fan-shaped body-round body type a neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-round body type a neuron (PFR_a) that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2. It targets the same (contralateral) column of the fan-shaped body as PFR_a neurons of the contralateral glomerulus 8, medial to the projection of the glomerulus 1 cell (Lin et al., 2013; Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It projects laterally from the fan-shaped body to the contralateral round body (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021).

definition.value: PB glomerulus 1 neuron described by Lin et al. (2013) includes both the glomerulus 1 and 2 neurons from Wolff et al. (2015) and later, due to identification of an additional medial PB glomerulus (checked by comparing wiring diagrams). This term refers to the glomerulus 2 neuron of Wolff et al. (2015). This corresponds to the Hanesch et al. (1989) 'horizontal fiber system' neuron of glomerulus 1 (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-round body type b neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-round body neuron that has a one-column ipsilateral phase-shift between the protocerebral bridge (PB) and the fan-shaped body (FB) (the PB glomerulus 5 cell maps to a column just ipsilateral of the central column) (Hulse et al., 2021). There are fewer of these cells than PFR_a cells and they collectively target fewer PB glomeruli (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-bilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Small field neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3 and in a column of the fan-shaped body, between the projections of the glomerulus 2 and 4 cells in the same hemisphere, mainly in layers 4 and 5, and axon terminals in the lateral accessory lobes of both hemispheres (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-bilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Small field neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5 and in the lateralmost column of the fan-shaped body in the same hemisphere, mainly in layers 4 and 5, and axon terminals in the lateral accessory lobes of both hemispheres (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 1-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-bilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Small field neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 1 and in a relatively medial column of the fan-shaped body, mainly in layers 4 and 5, and axon terminals in the lateral accessory lobes of both hemispheres (Lin et al., 2013; Hulse et al., 2021).

definition.value: Some of these cells may target the central column, some may target the same column as the glomerulus 2 cells of the same hemisphere (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 1-ipsilateral fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-unilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-unilateral lateral accessory lobe (PFL3) neuron with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge (PB) glomerulus 1 and in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body, in the same column as the ipsilateral PFL3 neuron of PB glomerulus 6 (Hulse et al., 2021). Its axon terminals are in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 1-contralateral fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-unilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-unilateral lateral accessory lobe (PFL3) neuron with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge (PB) glomerulus 1 and in the contralateral fan-shaped body, in the same column as the contralateral PFL3 neuron of PB glomerulus 5 (Lin et al., 2013; Hulse et al., 2021). Its axon terminals are in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (Lin et al., 2013; Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-unilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body layers 4 and 5-unilateral lateral accessory lobe (PFL3) neuron with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge (PB) glomerulus 2 (Hulse et al., 2021). There are two subtypes, one that targets the ipsilateral fan-shaped body (FB) and PB, and one that targets the contralateral FB and PB (Lin et al., 2013; Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: gall surround

value.value: Poorly defined region surrounding the gall that houses the arbors of some central complex neurons (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). Synapses of some neurons in this region have an elongated-bar morphology and contain dense core vesicles, suggestive of neuropeptide or neuromodulator release (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: dorsal gall surround

value.value: Poorly defined region surrounding the dorsal gall that houses the arbors of the adult ellipsoid body-dorsal gall surround neurons (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: ventral gall surround

value.value: Poorly defined region surrounding the ventral gall that houses the arbors of protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround neurons (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround (PFGs) neuron that targets protocerebral bridge (PB) glomerulus 2. It targets a relatively lateral contralateral fan-shaped body column, which is also targeted by the contralateral PFGs neuron of PB glomerulus 8 (Hulse et al., 2021). It projects to the contralateral ventral gall surround (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround (PFGs) neuron that targets protocerebral bridge (PB) glomerulus 3. It targets a contralateral fan-shaped body column, which is also targeted by the contralateral PFGs neuron of PB glomerulus 7 (Hulse et al., 2021). It projects to the contralateral ventral gall surround (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-ventral gall surround (PFGs) neuron that targets protocerebral bridge (PB) glomerulus 6. It targets a relatively medial ipsilateral fan-shaped body column, which is also targeted by the contralateral PFGs neuron of PB glomerulus 4 (Hulse et al., 2021). It projects to the contralateral ventral gall surround (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in an ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively lateral ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 9-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 9 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the lateralmost ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 9-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 9 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the lateralmost ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in an ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively medial ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the central column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively medial contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 4-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 4 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively lateral contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 ventral domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 2 dorsal domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the lateralmost contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 anterior domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 anterior domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the lateralmost contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the lateralmost contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively lateral contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 4-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 4 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively medial contralateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the central column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively medial ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in a relatively lateral ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: protocerebral bridge glomerulus 9-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron

value.value: Protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-fan-shaped body-nodulus 3 medial domain neuron that targets protocerebral bridge glomerulus 9 (Wolff et al., 2015; Hulse et al., 2021). It arborizes in the lateralmost ipsilateral column of the fan-shaped body (Hulse et al., 2021).

label.value: adult superior medial protocerebrum-bilateral lateral accessory lobe neuron

value.value: Adult neuron that has postsynaptic sites in the ipsilateral superior medial protocerebrum and lateral accessory lobe and presynaptic sites in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (Franconville et al., 2018).

definition.value: Franconville et al. (2018) list 2 subclasses (referred to as SMPL-L and SMPL-L2), but do not make it clear how these differ.

label.value: adult lateral accessory lobe-fan-shaped body layer 3 neuron

value.value: Adult neuron with mainly postsynaptic sites in the dorsolateral lateral accessory lobe, with some dendritic extensions into the nearby protocerebrum, and arborization spanning layer 3 of the fan-shaped body, consisting of mainly presynaptic sites (Franconville et al., 2018; Hulse et al., 2021). There are approximately four of these cells per hemisphere (Franconville et al., 2018; Hulse et al., 2021).

definition.value: Hemibrain FB3C closest match to Franconville et al. (2018) IMPL-F based on arborization pattern, cell number and soma location in Hulse et al. (2021) and Neuprint. Also similar to FB3D, but only 1 FB3D cell and FB3D very similar to FB3C.

label.value: adult olfactory antennal lobe glomerulus

value.value: Glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe that receives input from olfactory neurons. There are approximately 51 of these per hemisphere (Bates et al., 2020).

label.value: adult thermosensory neuron

value.value: Any adult neuron (FBbt:00047095) that is capable of some detection of temperature stimulus involved in thermoception (GO:0050960).

label.value: larval thermosensory neuron

value.value: Any larval neuron (FBbt:00001446) that is capable of some detection of temperature stimulus involved in thermoception (GO:0050960).

label.value: adult SFS neuron

value.value: Neuron that integrates excitatory and inhibitory inputs from MBON12 and MBON4, respectively (Lei et al., 2022). It synapses onto and can activate ventral fan-shaped body neurons (Lei et al., 2022). It is involved in post-learning sleep and long-term memory formation (Lei et al., 2022).

definition.value: Unclear from Lei et al. (2022) what 'SFS' stands for.
